claim.claim-text:
A method of forming a composite sheet material, comprising the steps of:
providing a substrate having a first face surface, a second face surface, and a plurality of edges, and which substrate includes a thermoplastic material;
providing a matrix that includes a support component and a thermoplastic component, wherein the support component has a first melting point and the thermoplastic component has a second melting point, and the second melting point is less than the first melting point;
positioning the substrate and the matrix such that the matrix is contiguous with the first face surface of the substrate; and
laminating the substrate and matrix together in a thermo-pressure process to form the composite sheet material.

The method of claim 1, further comprising the steps of:
providing a cover sheet that imparts one or more surface characteristics to the composite sheet material during thermo-pressure formation of the composite sheet material;
positioning the cover sheet on a side of the matrix that is opposite the side contiguous with the substrate;
subjecting the cover sheet to the thermo-pressure process within the laminating step;
wherein the support component is non-woven and wherein the support component comprises one or more of polyester, nylon, polyphenylsulfide, aromatic polyamide, fiberglass, polytetrafluoroethylene, wool, carbon fiber, Alumina/Silica, polyamide, polypropylene, polyethylene, cellulose, rayon, and viscose, or combinations thereof;
wherein the cover sheet comprises one or more polymeric materials selected from the group consisting of: polyamide, polyphenylsulfone, polyphenylsulfide, polyurethane, polyethylene, low-density polyethylene, polyamide-imide, ionomer, polycarbonate, polyethylene terephthalate, polybutylene terephthalate, fluoropolymers, and co-polymers thereof;
wherein the thermoplastic component substantially consists of one or more polymeric materials selected from the group consisting of polypropylene, polyethylene, polyethylene terephthalate, low-density polyethylene, polyurethane, polyamide, polyamide- imide, ionomer, acrylic, Surlyn Reflections®, and metallocene;
wherein after lamination the cover sheet is adhered to the matrix in a manner that allows removal of the cover sheet from the composite sheet material post formation to reveal the surface characteristic of the matrix; and
wherein the surface characteristic is at least one of a high gloss finish, a matte finish, a pebbled finish, a satin finish, and a gloss finish.

The method of claim 1, further comprising the steps of:
providing a cover sheet that imparts one or more surface characteristics to the composite sheet material during thermo-pressure formation of the composite sheet material;
positioning the cover sheet on a side of the matrix;
subjecting the cover sheet to the thermo-pressure process within the laminating step;
wherein the support component is selected from the group consisting of non-woven polyester, non-woven fiberglass, non-woven polyamide, and combinations thereof;
wherein the cover sheet comprises one or more polymeric materials selected from the group consisting of polyamide, polyester, polypropylene, polyethylene and combinations and co-polymers thereof;
wherein the thermoplastic component substantially consists of selected from the group consisting of polypropylene, polyethylene, polyamide and combinations and copolymers thereof;
wherein after lamination the cover sheet is adhered to the matrix in a manner that allows removal of the cover sheet from the composite sheet material post formation to reveal the surface characteristic of the matrix; and
wherein the surface characteristic is at least one of a high gloss finish, a matte finish, a pebbled finish, a satin finish, and a gloss finish.
